
Preheat oven to 425 F. Melt 3 tbsp butter in a 10" ovenproof frying pan over 
low heat. Remove from heat.

In a large bowl or blender, beat or whirl 3 eggs until pale. Beat or blend in 
3/4 c milk, 1/2 tsp vanilla, 1/2 c + 1 tbsp flour, 2 tbsp sugar, and 1/8 tsp
salt. 

Pour batter into prepared pan and bake until puffed and lightly browned, 15-20
minutes. Top with powdered sugar and lemon juice, or slice into wedges and 
serve with jelly.


Ingredients:
3 tbsp butter
3 eggs
3/4 c milk
1/2 tsp vanilla
1/2 c + 1 tbsp white flour
2 tbsp sugar
1/8 tsp salt

